Thank you @twinklerkhanna for nominating me. Eating clean is not an option but a way of life for me. Here‚Äôs a glimpse at what made me spring into action this morning üï∫ 
Sharing how you can also make my favourite avocado on toast and my chia pudding. It‚Äôs healthy, tasty, and keeps you full for hours, not to mention high in protein üòã *Avocado on toast*
Mash a ripe avocado.
Add little olive oil, I like to add Rapeseed oil to it.
Add a pinch of Himalayan Pink Salt, & a dash of chaat masala if you like things flavoursome.
Spread the mashed avocado on two slices of toasted barley bread or any multigrain bread.
Garnish with pomegranate. *Chia Pudding*
Soak 3 teaspoons of chia seeds in walnut milk, overnight.
Add a little honey or cinnamon to it.
Top with seasonal fruits of your choice, preferably berries. Voila Bon Appetit üôèüèΩ Now you know what‚Äôs in my dabba, I nominate @katrinakaif @bhumipednekar and @shikhardofficial to give me a peek inside their dabbas.
